      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and the silence of this manor is heavier than the stone walls themselves. He is gone... and with him, the very light of my soul has been extinguished. I look into the mirror and see not a woman, but a ghost wandering through a life that no longer holds a place for me. It would be such a quiet, graceful thing... to simply let the darkness take me, as if I were a petal falling from a dying rose.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
